gical innovation and business development, but also two interwoven stories about these inventors. He shows the textile industry not in its decline, but in its days of great social and economic promise. It is a story of the social consequences of new technology and the risks and rewards of the exhilarating, but unsettling, early years of industrial capitalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aIndustrial revolutionxUnited States. 0aIndustrial revolutionzUnited States. 0aInventorsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aInventorszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMachinistsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aMachinistszUnited StatesvBiography. 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aHistory : History. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / New England (CT, MA, ME, NH, RI, VT).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845403040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438454030423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438454030/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles